},"cardImage":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1614071659313-fd1bb53ce2a9?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxDaHVyYXVtaSUyMEFxdWFyaXVtJTIwd2hhbGUlMjBzaGFya3xlbnwxfDB8fHwxNzgzMzcxODg1fDA&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080"}],"top10":[{"rank":1,"name":"Tokyo","placeId":"tokyo","regionId":"kanto","regionName":"Kantō","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1604928141064-207cea6f571f?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxUb2t5byUyMGNpdHlzY2FwZSUyMG5lb24lMjBsaWdodHN8ZW58MXwwfHx8MTc4MzM2ODE4MHww&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Takashi Miyazaki"},"description":"Japan's capital and largest metropolitan area, blending ultra-modern skyscrapers with historic temples and traditional neighborhoods. Essential for experiencing contemporary Japanese culture, world-class museums, shopping, and dining across distinct districts like Shibuya, Shinjuku, and Asakusa."},{"rank":2,"name":"Kyoto","placeId":"kyoto","regionId":"kansai","regionName":"Kansai","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1616666720738-0f4dbf0d3e9f?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxGdXNoaW1pJTIwSW5hcmklMjB0b3JpaSUyMGdhdGVzfGVufDF8MHx8fDE3ODMzNjgyNDR8MA&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Lucas Calloch"},"description":"Japan's ancient capital with over 2,000 temples, traditional wooden machiya houses, and the iconic torii gates of Fushimi Inari. This is the cultural heart of Japan and essential for experiencing traditional temples, gardens, geisha districts, and kaiseki cuisine."},{"rank":3,"name":"Osaka","placeId":"osaka","regionId":"kansai","regionName":"Kansai","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1596240748549-6ec0f32d4c95?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxPc2FrYSUyMENhc3RsZXxlbnwxfDB8fHwxNzgzMzY4MjQ2fDA&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Jeremy Santana"},"description":"Japan's vibrant second city known for its street food, nightlife, and Osaka Castle with spectacular views. The energetic atmosphere, excellent food scene (takoyaki, okonomiyaki), and modern shopping districts make it a dynamic contrast to Kyoto's serenity."},{"rank":4,"name":"Mount Fuji","placeId":"mt_fuji","regionId":"kanto","regionName":"Kantō","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1623555113026-876478ee75b6?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxNb3VudCUyMEZ1amklMjBzbm93JTIwcGVha3xlbnwxfDB8fHwxNzgzMzY4MTg4fDA&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Matt Palmer"},"description":"Japan's iconic snow-capped volcano and UNESCO World Heritage site, visible from Tokyo on clear days and climbable during summer season. The sacred mountain is fundamental to Japanese identity and offers spectacular hiking, views from surrounding lakes, and spiritual significance."},{"rank":5,"name":"Hiroshima","placeId":"hiroshima","regionId":"kansai","regionName":"Kansai","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1650219813736-d823a037af22?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxIaXJvc2hpbWElMjBQZWFjZSUyME1lbW9yaWFsfGVufDF8MHx8fDE3ODMzNjgyNTR8MA&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"T L"},"description":"Home to the poignant Hiroshima Peace Memorial Park and Museum dedicated to WWII history and promoting peace. The site is deeply meaningful, offering important historical context and beautiful riverside gardens that inspire reflection on humanity."},{"rank":6,"name":"Hakone","placeId":"hakone","regionId":"kanto","regionName":"Kantō","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1509023464722-18d996393ca8?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxIYWtvbmUlMjBNb3VudCUyMEZ1amklMjByZWZsZWN0aW9uJTIwbGFrZXxlbnwxfDB8fHwxNzgzMzY4MTkxfDA&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Clay Banks"},"description":"Mountain resort town famous for hot springs, scenic mountain scenery, and views of Mount Fuji across its volcanic lake. Popular for relaxation, hiking, and open-air art museums, with excellent onsen (hot spring) experiences and mountain railway attractions."},{"rank":7,"name":"Nara","placeId":"nara","regionId":"kansai","regionName":"Kansai","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1699908894842-1d0eec54672e?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxOYXJhJTIwR3JlYXQlMjBCdWRkaGF8ZW58MXwwfHx8MTc4MzM2ODI1Mnww&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Peter Amende"},"description":"Ancient capital home to the massive bronze Daibutsu (Great Buddha) in Todai-ji Temple and hundreds of friendly, bowing deer roaming Nara Park. This UNESCO World Heritage site offers remarkable temples, spacious parks, and a relaxed atmosphere perfect for a day trip from Kyoto."},{"rank":8,"name":"Sapporo","placeId":"sapporo","regionId":"hokkaido","regionName":"Hokkaido","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1738246903414-79643a0c9b9e?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxTYXBwb3JvJTIwc25vdyUyMGZlc3RpdmFsfGVufDF8MHx8fDE3ODMzNjQ2NjF8MA&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Dominic Kurniawan Suryaputra"},"description":"Hokkaido's vibrant capital city known for its grid-pattern streets, ramen culture, and snow festival. A modern urban hub with excellent museums, shopping, and dining that serves as the gateway to exploring the island."},{"rank":9,"name":"Tokyo Disney Resort","placeId":"tokyo_disneyland","regionId":"kanto","regionName":"Kantō","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1565839751802-33cd9264527c?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxUb2t5byUyMERpc25leSUyMFJlc29ydCUyMEphcGFufGVufDF8MHx8fDE3ODQwMjU4MDd8MA&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Colton Jones"},"description":"Comprised of Tokyo Disneyland and DisneySea theme parks, this resort is one of the world's most visited amusement park destinations. It offers unique attractions and entertainment that appeal to families and visitors of all ages."},{"rank":10,"name":"Takayama","placeId":"takayama","regionId":"chugoku","regionName":"Chūgoku","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1764672277000-5b30f1067b99?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxUYWtheWFtYSUyMG9sZCUyMHRvd24lMjBwcmVzZXJ2ZWR8ZW58MXwwfHx8MTc4MzM2ODMwNHww&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Airu"},"description":"Though in Gifu, this mountain town is essential for Chugoku travelers seeking traditional Japanese character with beautifully preserved merchant houses and sake breweries. The town features morning markets, mountain scenery, and provides access to Shirakawa-go village for deep cultural immersion."}]}